{"product_id": "39190", "page": 9, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-09-29", "text": "I was happy to see this game again--one of my favorites. Unfortunately the game does not do well with Windows 10. Tends to drop you or freeze up, up to a complete restart. You might also end up on the \"end\" of the map--there's more territory to get to, but the trail ends  in blank squares to nothingness.\nSteam has never disappointed me before. I will not abandon such an amazing service over a hiccup in one game that's over a decade old. I only paid $1.99! I don't even want a refund. Steam people, you are the BEST. This game just doesn't work.", "hours": 3.1, "user_id": "76561197982378624", "username": "Vesalius", "products": 33, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 9, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-09-29", "text": "Be aware : I may be a bit biased since this game was a really nice part of me growing up, so nostalgia may be a factor here.\nHowever this game is A REAL GEM, lovely mechanics, a nice story, pretty nice characters that you'll most likely remember a long time after playing this, great soundtrack and sounddesign which means adaptable sound depending on the scenario.\nApart from that this game will give you good bang for the buck (I did pick it up during a 75% discount period), but even at regular price this would be a good deal.\nIF you keep in mind that it's an older game, however I find the graphics to hold up pretty amazingly, it's definitely playable.\nSome complaints: the expansion for this game was a really big one and changed the game immensely--> problem--> it's not included nor is it possible to buy it on steam !!!! :(\nSo no 'legends of Arana' :'(\nThe resolution is quite poor (but that is to be expected)\nThe AI is pretty horrible, so the best experience might be had playing this without companions.\nThe multiplayer mode doesn't work, but people may have found ways around that online.\nApart from that, it works when you start it, which can't be said about the steam version of 'dungeon siege II' (see my review from that game if you want.\nI still would advice to give this a try since it's a really nice game, that's also the reason why I still fondly remember it from a long time ago, and it holds up to my nostalgia.", "hours": 1.7, "user_id": "76561198047585088", "username": "I'm f'd up and that's ok", "products": 243, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 9, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-09-29", "text": "It's a shame no work has been done to make this run on modern screens. The low res I could put up with, but there's no option for windowed mode. If you set fullscreen=false as a launch option it works, but then there's graphics artifacting all over the screen. Can't alt tab or close the game properly after switching either. A shame, used to be a great game!", "hours": 1.0, "username": "Ishvii", "products": 330, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 9, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-09-27", "text": "This is a classic staple in the Action/RPG genre. In my mind, it may be more basic than Diablo or Baldur's Gate, but it has unique qualities about it that make it stand out in my mind. It may be old, it may have a lacking story, but overall it is a fun experience that anyone who considers themselves a fan of RPGs should pick up and kill time playing.", "hours": 10.6, "user_id": "76561198040710188", "username": "CartmanTuttle | Assist Co.", "products": 153, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 9, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-09-26", "text": "First: go into the file directory and change the compatability mode to Windows XP\nI loved this game when it was new (before I had Steam) and continue to play it from time to time.  I admit I prefer the Cat Mansion mod, but even without that it's a very good example of the genre.\nAutomated attack allows a casual aspect and control of up to 6 characters allows for playing around with character development.  The story is pretty straight forward and there's not much descision making, but, if one were suficiently dedicated, there is an editor that could be used to create whatever plot line and world archetcture desired.\nThe game is dated and doesn't always run on modern systems (thus the compatibility mode suggestion) and it barrowed heavily from Diablo for equipment style.  That said, it was a great game in it's time.  Fully modable, seamless area transitions, multiple characters, side quests, network play; the game had LOTs of potential.\nIt has its flaws.  It easily could have been more dynamic with both story and NPC interaction.  The lack of a more open world or re-spawning monsters made progression limited, but again, the editor allowed for all of that.  I suppose the game itself could have been more fully developed by the developer, but at the time the focus was on encouraging an active modding community (which was a true novelty when the game was released).\nUltimately it's the casual control style that keeps me coming back to this one.  This game is fun to play.", "hours": 51.9, "user_id": "76561198011676953", "username": "papacat_bartlett", "products": 310, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 9, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-09-25", "text": "An outstanding game that I played years ago and lost the software over time.  I picked up the collection at Humble Bundle and redeemed it here on Steam.  I just finished the game moments ago(Win10-64bit@720p max playable w/o quirks) and highly reccomend this very underrated game.\nUnfortunately when it was originally released it was up against the massive powerhouse known as the Baldur's Gate franchise.  And it faded in comparison (as did so many other cRPG's) during the years of the late 90's to around a decade after that when Baldur's Gate ruled cRPG's.\nPick up this game and enjoy.  Watch some 'Youtube' vids for gaming assistance/guides or the forum here!\nFor my use I created a shortcut link and added the resolution to the command line for best playability on my PC.", "hours": 76.6, "user_id": "76561198060087332", "username": "Lord Draco", "products": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 9, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-09-24", "text": "I bought this game expecting to have a blast. But instead I get \"Excpetion found!\" message and shortly afterwards, the game crashes.  I've tried to find ways to fix it. NOTHING. Not worth going through the hassle.", "hours": 0.5, "user_id": "76561198406278336", "username": "Nakigara1985", "products": 8, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 9, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-09-23", "text": "This is one of my favorite games. I still play it regularly. I am not coordinated enough for first person shooters so these hack and slash quest games are great. I especially like the little details like the doe and fawn in the forest that bounds away as you approach. I really like the 360 degree look around.  Wis there was more of this type.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "lbest1", "products": 5, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 9, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-09-22", "text": "So..... it crashed during the opening into cinematic. Multiple times,  without fail.\nBetween that and the Expansion not being on Steam, so you can't even play the whole game.... meh, you can do better things with your time. I mean, I'd be\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665about now if I couldn't refund the thing. Too bad, I was optimistic on this one.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "Toastasaurus Rex", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
