{"product_id": "39190", "page": 14, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-22", "text": "Bought this game since I remember enjoying it quite a bit in the good ol' days. Disappointed though. Why would steam make you pay for something that does not work properly with more recent OS's? There is a round-about way of making it work, but it seems to be more trouble than it's worth. Surely they could figure out a way to patch the game to run better, or at least give us a warning that it's not compatible (as I did not see the warning when I purchased it).\nGood game from what I remember, but not fun buying it, dling it and then discovering it doesnt work 100%", "hours": 0.3, "username": "Blitzkit", "products": 106, "early_access": false}
