{"product_id": "39190", "page": 15, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-17", "text": "It is a very good and fun to play hack and slash game, it has no rpg elements but still feels like one. Thing is i played and finished it when it was kinda newly released BUT with a Win10x64 o.s. it is nothing but trouble. Even totally locked up my pc while playing it. Task manager, alt+tab, ctrl+alt+delete had no effect.\nIF YOU DON'T HAVE A PC WITH WIN XP AND OLD HARDWARE AVOID BUYING IT. (Dungeon Siege 2 is an even better game but it have same issues either)", "hours": 37.7, "user_id": "76561198084571740", "username": "LukeDrunkwalker", "products": 134, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 15, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-14", "text": "Square Enix and Gas Powered Games should be ashamed of themselves for attempting to sell this game.  The entire thing is glitched and not compatable with newer windows systems.  This should have a disclaimer that it is NOT compatible with windows 10.  This is a shame because I am sure I would enjoy this game a great deal.", "hours": 3.2, "username": "Jayce Ran", "products": 670, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 15, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-11", "text": "Great game, bought it for nostalgia.\nUnfortunately steam doesn't provide the expansion pack, but some how does allow piracy promoting topics on the community board.\nBut If you're in to classic rpg's and don't mind long grinds and 100% RNG than this could be a game right up your alley.\nThe lore is great and the graphic design is top notch for its time ( in my opinion ) various sceneries and many hidden treassures and other secrets and tons of side quests and even audio dialogue!\nNOTE: if you're relatively young or just can't stand poor graphics or challening slow pased gameplay, save your buck for the next COD.", "hours": 2.3, "user_id": "76561198070210099", "username": "-Wiggle-", "products": 37, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 15, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-10", "text": "Perfect game.\nWhen it's complete.\nThis version is missing the DLC, which adds so much to it.\nI'd recommend pirating or something because it's just not worth playing without all the content.", "hours": 23.5, "username": "Sassy Beard", "products": 373, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 15, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-05", "text": "It's unfortunate that this is missing the Aranna expansion but it's still an amazing game. I remember when I was 12 and my dad had this game for his computer. It was the only rpg game he had and he let me play it. I remember the graphics were amazing and the gameplay was amazing and it was just amazing. Now, I actually have the physical copy with the expansion but Steam gave me this when I pre-ordered Dungeon Siege 3 and since I have a newish computer and I'm lazy and don't want to be bothered with disks I played it through Steam. The graphics have... not aged well but if you can get passed that and the bugs and the lack of optimization for newer machines, this is still an amazing game. It's a blend of Diablo and Baldur's Gate and you level up your skills by using them. ie: You want to get better at swords so you use a sword more to level that skill up. If you don't have the patience for an old game that crashes occasionally then you might want to give this a pass but if you don't mind then definitely pick this up!", "hours": 7.0, "username": "Audasaurus Rex", "products": 656, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 15, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-05-22", "text": "Assuming it works for you, yes, absolutely I recommend this game.  It's an extremely well designed game that plays like a cross between Diablo and Baldur's Gate.  Combat is quick and accessible, yet still strategic enough that you can and should use the real-time-pause feature.  And unlike a lot of older WRPGs, you don't have to worry too much about screwing up your character build.  You get seven more characters total, and health slowly regenerates even if you run out of potions or healing spells.\nThe caveat with this game is if it'll work for you.  I'm blessed, I have Windows 10 and it works perfectly for me out of the box as far as I can tell, but as you can see with other reviews, that's hardly the case for everyone.\nStill, this isn't an especially story heavy game.  Two hours should be more than enough to tell if you'll like it and it'll work or not.  So definitely give this one a try.", "hours": 2.9, "user_id": "76561197971305233", "username": "Runie", "products": 680, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 15, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-05-22", "text": "Wasted money. Cant even play the game without it crashing.", "hours": 101.9, "user_id": "76561197977604561", "username": "garyntx", "products": 14, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 15, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-05-17", "text": "i love this game when i was a wee hatchling. finally got a hold of it again and just went ham and let me tell you, its so damn enjoyable. Love this damn game, absolute vintage stuff, i mean the graphics are abit dated but its still enjoyable, by yourself, with a few mates its awesome anyway your slice it.\n10/10 would recommend", "hours": 53.1, "user_id": "76561198286950224", "username": "TheTrueBigKahuna", "products": 8, "early_access": false}
