{"product_id": "39190", "page": 18, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-09", "text": "One of the few realy good point n click / hack n slash rpgs out there.\nWorth every dime if you enjoy that sort of game.\nNow im not gonna give a big page of why this game is good. Reason is, one could say my mind is clouded with so much good nostalgia that i cant give a reasonable review about its pros and cons.\nBut being a \"patron\" of this game, jumping in and out doing some replays now and then with varieties of mods and siegelets i still cant stop loving this game.\nIv played the CD version since i was a teenager and got a way more disturbing amount of hours ingame than displayed on steam, it has stuck to me like a good book you go back to now and then.\nIf you are a Diablo fan or any other P'n'C/H'n'S rpg fan i strongly recommend you play this one out.", "hours": 12.0, "username": "Grana", "products": 223, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 18, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-05", "text": "Love this game. It is a classic. However, if you are running a modern system it will probably crash at some point. Whether that is during game play, or after you save your first game, shut down, and then try to load again, something will go wrong. This game isn't really supported well so you will need to hunt down fixes online to make it work. If you do get it to work, good on ya! If you don't, well, you were warned. I do wish Steam would make a bigger effort when allowing these types of older games onto the sytem to support them and make sure they work always.", "hours": 1.0, "user_id": "76561197998239912", "username": "SvenCadillac", "products": 24, "early_access": false}
