{"product_id": "39190", "page": 19, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-26", "text": "Runs fine on a Windows 10 64x Rig.\nNaturally there are a few minor tweeks to do before starting your game, but this take no-longer than five minutes to do.\nIve finished the game without any crash2desktop moments, and even have it installed on a windows 10 86x machine with crappy intergrated GFX. (it has crashed on the 86x machine, but this is most likely down to bad hardware, not the game).\n10/10 still lives up to the nostalgia, and still very playable.", "hours": 10.0, "username": "Count_Chamberlain", "products": 219, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 19, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-24", "text": "Was my first RPG back in 2002 (yes I started late) and I loved it. I would recommend it every day just for the extremely nice soundtrack by Jeremy Soule, this is unreal how good it is!", "hours": 6.6, "username": "JackMayol", "products": 73, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 19, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-22", "text": "Cult Classic!", "hours": 5.4, "user_id": "76561198047384882", "username": "Penitenziagite", "products": 2430, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 19, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-16", "text": "Enjoyed many aspects to this game and the graphics held up alright many moons later. The story wasn't the most interesting and the hardest part of the game was figuring out a way to balancing your party as there is limited foes and experience points out there to share-- once that was figured out, it was fairly easy afterwards with a few challenging parts. The music is very comfy and familiar, the loot was interesting, and the environments as well as enemies were varied and often intriguing. For a game call Dungeon Siege, I can't recall going thru more than a couple of actual dungeons, but I guess Rolling Valley & Swamp Siege doesn't roll off the tongue well. The game didn't seem to have any bugs, though sometimes I had to switch resolutions so it would fit properly, but that might be an OS thing anyway. If you like RPGs with multiple party members you can use simultaneously, you will most likely have a good time. Considering it's age, the game is great value at 5 dollars or less.", "hours": 120.4, "user_id": "76561198258961223", "username": "massivered", "products": 90, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 19, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-13", "text": "Good solid game with a nice soundtrack, offers interesting combat/encounters a unusually big party with up to 8 members that you can customize with various random loot and spells that drop, only negative aspects i found are that in some area's the camera controls are clumsy and the overall story isnt flashed out enough, coming to a unsatisfying conclusion.", "hours": 50.8, "user_id": "76561198043006337", "username": "Kztfv", "products": 423, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 19, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-08", "text": "One of the classics of my childhood. Loved the game back then as I do now.\nGraphics are obviously outdated but for a sale-price of 1,49\u20ac there is nothing to do wrong if you're into RPG's.\nGameplay:\nIts a group based, real time RPG/hack&slay with different class systems.\n(Warrior, Archer, Nature-magic sorcerer, Destructive-magic sorcerer)\nEach class plays their own part in the group of up to 8 characters.\nIn addition you can add a mule to your group in exchange for one character spot.\nThe mule serves as a bigger storage for items.\nOn \"easy\" the game can be enjoyed without worrying much, a healing spell there and a healthpotion on another place and you're fine to go. You'll get through the game within 10-12h.\nOn \"normal\" the game will take you essentially longer and will force you into micro-managing your group throughout combat, using the pause button and rearranage targets, positions of your group members and abilities used! (especially the mages!)\nI didn't have the guts to sit through on \"hard\" yet... but it's a challange if you want it to be!\n+ Many different items and spells (with different looks and animations)\n+ Many different races, enemies and landscapes to explore\n+ Audio-voiced story line and NPC's\n+ Modded multiplayer does still work (I recommend tunngle)\n+ Nostalgica (for me!)\n+ Low price\n- Hard-mode is \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ttery difficult as splash damage wipes you the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 out\n- That \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing blue-fire trap-chest at the shore in front of the dark forest\n10/10", "hours": 22.2, "username": "jmB", "products": 194, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 19, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-07", "text": "Do you like an RPG that has no class system, letting you build as YOU want?\nDo you like a story-based game, with none of those silly lame romance tropes?\nDo you want to be shoved right into the action, with simple controls that are easy to learn, yet hard to master?\nDo you like shooting chickens out of a minigun?\nThis is the RPG for you. 11/10 would feel the Ehb and Flow of this game again.", "hours": 17.1, "user_id": "76561198070332611", "username": "Fenix", "products": 86, "found_funny": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 19, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-04", "text": "Windows 10, game works for me. It's still playable, no widescreen resolution though. Sound effects are terrible and the graphics obviously dated. Game is also a lot easier to play from the 1-dimensional overlay map than the actual 3d-environment, since you have a better vision of what's going on and it's a lot easier to click on enemies. You will be playing this for nostalgia, if at all, though.", "hours": 0.9, "user_id": "76561197992229015", "username": "Dire", "products": 542, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 19, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-01", "text": "Lets me explain it as simple as this...\n\"Dungeon Siege\" and \"Dungeon Siege II\" are superb and brillant games\n, it is a shame their is no multiplayer option on Steam, which like all other players of this game I am disgruntled about.\nWith that exception, you want to push this game on the higher settings more and more, and it is a shame there is no impossible setting to try.\nAwesome!\nNow \"Dungeon Siege III\", is an unbelievable disappointment that carries no elements of it's predecessors.\nStick with the first two in the series, and mentally rename the third to not taint the titles.\n-Universal Gamer", "hours": 66.2, "user_id": "76561198067563194", "username": "Universal Gamer", "products": 91, "early_access": false}
