{"product_id": "39190", "page": 23, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-24", "text": "This is one of the first rpgs that I remember playing through to completion, and I loved it when I was younger. I recently began playing through it again as a let's play for my YouTube channel (JadekindVideoGaming if interested). I am still enjoying the game, however it has not aged as well as I might have hoped. There have been several technical issues with the game crashing or not loading saves, which have caused some frustration. Additionally, I feel parts of the game drag on for too long, and that there are general pacing issues.\nAll that said, I am still enjoying the game as a trip through memory lane. I would recomend this game, yes, but as an older game you should certainly know what you're getting yourself into when you begin.", "hours": 35.9, "username": "cat0claws", "products": 211, "early_access": false}
