{"product_id": "39190", "page": 34, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-14", "text": "Why isn't the 1.50 version with Legends of Aranna available on Steam from the beginning? It fixes a number of issues the base game including improved itemization and more reactive AI.\nIf it wasn't for a guide telling you to activate the LoA expansion I'd be hard pressed to really recommend the game because of those issues.\nGranted the camera is still awful, even worse in the LoA campaign but it's almost a minor issue compared to the things that it fixes or improves.", "hours": 47.5, "username": "Cooked Auto", "products": 199, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 34, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-13", "text": "I love this game. It's my favorite PC game, period.\nI highly reccomend this game. BUT I DO NOT reccomend buying it on here if you have Windows 8. It's a waste of money.  I I spent a long time trying to figure out how to get it to stop crashing BEFORE even getting to the main menu. Finally I got there but Single Player and Multiplayer are crashing still. Multiplayer crashes before entering the game and single player crashes during the opening scene. There's 7 bucks I'll never get back. For a game that won't run. Thank you, Steam.", "hours": 0.8, "user_id": "76561198082829353", "username": "Kirby0770", "products": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 34, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-11", "text": "Watch Ross's game dungeon on this game. My only advice after that is to play it when you have alot of free time, its best to play through in the span of a short period of time. Also after you beat the main game you can enable the expansion using mods, and using even more mods you can play the multiplayer in singleplayer. If theres some things I dont like about the game its that caves and dungeons go on for longer than I like and they are really close togeather, ontop of that 2/3rd of the way through each dungeon/cave I keep thinking \"Man, will this ever end\". Other wise this is a fantastic game, I highly recomend it.", "hours": 32.1, "username": "Qwibblez", "products": 309, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 34, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-10", "text": "Dungeon Siege is a great game, but the Steam release is ludicrously hobbled. As a matter of fact, there is no way to bu the expansion pack for this game on Steam... or to really get the game to work correctly at all, as it turns out. I have about 45 minutes logged with this Steam reease and I'm honestly wondering how, because I sure as hell can't get it to work.\nEven if you have an older rig that can run this game, you're better off looking for a boxed copy. Retail price is $6, and I can't recommend it, even for 75% off. Avoid.", "hours": 0.8, "username": "Ground Man", "products": 717, "early_access": false}
