{"product_id": "39190", "page": 36, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-27", "text": "Dungeon Siege was one of the first games I remember playing, and while it's starting to show its age, it's still very playable today.  Unfortunately, the Steam version contains a few odd features (broken cutscenes and no multiplayer among them) but overall I would strongly suggest purchasing Dungeon Siege if it's on sale, it's a great game to lose a weekend to.\nPros:\nClassic game with excellent replayability\nMassive modding community\nCons:\nNo multiplayer on steam version\nCan be a hassle to run on newer versions of Windows", "hours": 26.4, "username": "TinShadowcat", "products": 16, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 36, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-12-26", "text": "I wanted to go through the dungeon siege serie, starting with this one, but... I stopped after Stonebridge.\nGame mechanics is old, graphics, while acceptable, are really outdated, and the story is quite hard to follow. It's just about point&click.\nPersonalisation of character is not developed (based on a usage system, the more you do something, the better you become, quite logic but it doesn't offer more than stats).\nRating: 7/20 - dungeon siege 2 seems to be more interesting, and as there is no link between the 2', better off starting directly there.", "hours": 2.9, "user_id": "76561198077623263", "username": "Elessar", "products": 161, "early_access": false}
