{"product_id": "39190", "page": 37, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-06", "text": "A good ol' game. Requires a few workarounds to work at its best on modern PCs but it is certainly a great game. If you like your typical DnD-style RPG games, well Dungeon Siege is in the same style but much more combat focused. You can have 8 dudes at once in a giant melee moshpit, and still find it difficult at a normal difficulty. The minigun doesn't do as much damage as I'd like.\nOn a scale of ham to vegetable, I'd say it's about pretzel.", "hours": 12.8, "username": "Fisherman Joe", "products": 345, "early_access": false}
