{"product_id": "39190", "page": 38, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-06", "text": "Great game. A lot like diablo. Dungeons are not instanced, so there is no loading. Its somewhat limited thought. Magic isn't elemental. Fire monsters take as much damage by fire spells as ice monsters. Its somewhat imbalanced, melee is overpowered. The party system and mules are awesome. I just love being able to control a party of heroes instead of only one, but at the same time not a whole army. It is like playing a truly rpg pen and paper by yourself where you control the whole party, or only one hero if you wish. Its not perfect, limited in a lot of aspects, but overall a very enjoyable game with unique features (afaik).", "hours": 0.1, "user_id": "76561197977433417", "username": "Lero", "products": 86, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 39, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-04", "text": "Love games before blanace? Love to break\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665over frustrating \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t? Like dark souls? Well this game is for you! Experience hours of dying and absolute \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t with dungeon siege! Glitchy bots that are dumb as \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665. Its an ok game about 10 years ago. Save your money and get Elder scrolls Skyrim.", "hours": 29.9, "user_id": "76561198058407540", "username": "KronicNXC", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
