{"product_id": "39190", "page": 49, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-07", "text": "The game is great, but it has a missing link, the expansion, even though Steam or Square Enix doesn't deliver the game expansion Legends of Aranna you can go to the ''Guides'' section on the Community Hub and easily enable it,\nJust as you can join our growing Steam group:\nand our Discord server:\nEven though i disagree with the lack of support from Square Enix, i will give a thumbs up since i've fixed their errors and also because the game is great.\nMy aim was always to keep this gem alive, i think i've may have succeeded a little bit.", "hours": 29.7, "username": "Killah", "products": 278, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 49, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-06", "text": "This game as well as it's first sequel are classics of their genre. As it is, as sold by Steam, I would not suggest purchasing the game. I played all the way through and what you're getting here is the bare minimum version of the game. It's bugged as it is, and while some glitches can be worked around with enough knowledge and personal tweaking, there are some things, like the missing ending video files after fighting the last boss that prevents you from obtaining his loot, and thelack of access to multiplayer that dampers just about the whole experience. It was fun while it lasted, but there's a better version of the game out there. Also, by default, no Legends of Aranna. Stick to the real deal. Again, I recommend this game and the first sequel, just not the way it's sold here, even if it is dirt cheap right now. Well, you get what you pay for I suppose.", "hours": 50.8, "username": "ToothlessApollo", "products": 13, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
