{"product_id": "39190", "page": 53, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "One of my all-time favorite games. I've played it through several times, and as a fantasy RPG/dungeon crawler, this game gets just about everything right. You start off as a solo adventurer fighting mobs, and looting treasure and weapons. Along the way, you meet more adventurers that join you in your quest. Ultimately, you end up with a party of six, and you choose how you want each person to develop their fighting style.\nOther D&D-style games like Baldur's Gate have a very steep learning curve, and are heavy on the player maintenance. I think that Dungeon Siege strikes just the right balance between playability and maintenance.", "hours": 52.0, "user_id": "76561197964682472", "username": "cajun", "products": 347, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 53, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-25", "text": "This Is Awesome!!!! :DD:D thats a classic one :D", "hours": 3.3, "user_id": "76561198070478777", "username": "JOHN CENAA", "products": 195, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 53, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-25", "text": "Hell yeah, any Steam friends of mine into MMORPG's or RPG's or MMO's or whatever the difference, this game is a flash back to the past. Very rustic, and old, dating back to 2002, I played this when I was like 6 or 7, and decided to play it again 12 years ago, it's even better than I thought. Not sure about Dungeon Siege 2, I played that as well 7 years ago or so, but it wasn't the same, it got pretty advanced and felt like WoW. It was still fun though.\nSo you guys should get Dungeon Siege, very diverse open world MMORPG,\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ton of different items and stuff. Focuses on a few branches of skills: Magic. which is Combat Magic and Nature Magic. Melee weapons, such as Maces, Swords, Clubs, Axes, Scythes and a lot more random stuff. Ranged weapons, like Bows, Crossbows, and I think there's even a laser gun at one point from a steampunk robot enemy you fight in the game.\nThe game gets really addicting, make sure you save frequently, it crashed about 20 hours in and I lost about an hours worth of progress.", "hours": 45.6, "username": "Fflewddur Fflam", "products": 65, "early_access": false}
