{"product_id": "39190", "page": 59, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-03", "text": "How to run Dungeon Siege on Windows 7/8/8.1 that will fix flickering and tearing\nSTAGE 1: Configure your graphic card setting via graphic card control panel\n1. Open your graphic card control panel\n2. Go to 3D setting\n3. Add \"dungeonsiege.exe\"\n4. Disable or turn off any 3D enhancement\n5. Click \"Apply\"\nSTAGE 2: Edit Steam Game Launcher\n1. Open Steam\n2. Right Click on Dungeon Siege\n3. Select Properties\n4. Uncheck \"Enable Steam Overlay while in game\"\n5. Click \"Set Launch Option...\"\n6. Enter this string\nbltonly=true width=1366 height=768\nNote: You change the width and height base on your system resolution\n7. Click \"Ok\"\n8. Create desktop shortcut\"\nSTAGE 3: Edit ini file\n1. Right click on Dungeon Siege shortcut on desktop\n2. Open File Location\n3. Run DSVideoConfig.exe\n4. Select any graphic card that dont have TnL\n5. Click OK\n6. Double click on DungeonSiege.ini\n7. Select the first line and copy\n8. Go to your Document folder\n9. Open Dungeon Siege folder\n10. Double click on DungeonSiege.ini\n11. Select the first line and paste\n12. Save\nStage 4: Edit Video Option ingame\n1. Run Dungeon Siege\n2. Select Options\n3. Change Shadow setting to \"None\"\n4. Select OK\nCredit:\nStage 1 & 4 = Razali Rambli\nStage 2 & 3 = Various source from internet", "hours": 2.7, "user_id": "76561198118823146", "username": "Razali Bin Rambli", "products": 129, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 59, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-01", "text": "If you loved playing these old microsoft Pc games than you woulnt need a review to tell you its fun, but if you never played these before, go with dungeon siege two.", "hours": 5.2, "user_id": "76561198069057930", "username": "HailToCaesar", "products": 196, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 60, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-29", "text": "This game is the essence of hack n slash. That is literally all you do. It gets very tedious, very quick. Granted, the graphics are very nice for its time and I enjoy them very much. Much of the scenery is very inspired and you can tell they took the time to make it very detailed.\nThat being said, the maps are beyond huge. It's so easy to get lost and it can get very frustrating, quick. If all you want to do is hack n slash. This is definitely for you. The party concept of this game is awesome! You can have 7 people total in your party including a pack mule to carry all of your inventory which is very convenient. You have 3 main skills, Strength, Dexterity and Intelligent. (Swordsman, Bows and Spells).\nI played roughly 4-6 hours total and got to chapter 4 out of 9 chapters. I also killed and explored EVERY bit of area as I worked my way towards 5, but it's just..so tedious. Honestly, it's fun for what it is and I'm hoping to finish it one day, but no rush. Lastly, the story is fine. It's pretty interesting and the side quests are fun, even though they are just done along the way. The only problem is again, the maps are so insanely huge you might skip it and not even know. Problem with that? No fast travel and if you're a 100% kinda guy. You will be gritting your teeth on the way back from Chp. back to 1.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "HaunterInk", "products": 24, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 60, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-29", "text": "Pretty awsome game for its age\nIts Diablo/Dragon Age gameplay style\nWould recommend highly\nBought it with the Dugeon Siege Collection for 4.99 euro in Summer Sale\n8/10", "hours": 4.1, "username": "Khrainos \ud83d\udc95", "products": 1532, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 60, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-29", "text": "The classic dungeon crawler lives!  Dungeon Siege remains one of the most dynamic, engaging and complex games in its genre and it plays smoother than ever on Steam.  Do not hesitate on this.  The price is great, even when it isn't on sale, and stands high among modern Dungeon Crawlers like Torchlight 2 and Diablo III.  If you are a fan of the genre, this is a must-play.\nLeveling is smooth and effortless, requiring little maintanence, as skills and stats level through use.  You start as a blank slate, and as you use weapons and spells, your stats and your proficiency in those attack types increases automatically, similar to something like modern Elder Scrolls games.  It's a fluid and fun style.  Add to that the strategy element of having AI-controlled companions fighting alongside you, who can take commands or be set up in formations with proiorities and focuses that you choose based on their stats, with a number of optional playable units to hire from towns and dungeons.\nThis is a fast game, too.  It has all the challenge you would expect from an entry in the genre and encourages exploration and experimentation as you progress through the game.  Do not hesitate to invest in this title.  It is one of the greatest PC games of all time and remains one of my all-time favorite Dungeon Crawlers of all time!", "hours": 4.7, "user_id": "76561198027364206", "username": "ikillomega", "products": 469, "early_access": false}
