{"product_id": "39190", "page": 63, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-04-13", "text": "Having played through DS1/2 before a few years ago, I got this as part of a package deal (DS1,2,3) and didn't notice that it didn't include all the DLC/xpacs. The game itself looks pretty horrible on modern hardware.\nIMHO if you're going to play Dungeon Siege 1 or 2, you play it with all the DLC/xpacs. Even more so if you're going to play it in multiplayer, which simply doesn't work as is in the STEAM version.\nIf anything, they probably bundled this to get people into buying DS3, which is nothing like Dungeon Siege 1 or 2.", "hours": 0.1, "user_id": "76561198025701675", "username": "Bhun", "products": 83, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 63, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-09", "text": "Amazing game! Diablos cousin dungeon Siege is a long easy-going game that is always fun to play. Has replay value. Your player can be a warrior, archer, nature magic wizard, or combat magic wizard. If you want you can make him/her a balance of all. Along the way you can have other NPC players join your cause.\nbe sure to hold on to that newbie knife in the begining if you want to go to chicken level :P", "hours": 38.8, "user_id": "76561198068817979", "username": "Rorschach", "products": 296, "early_access": false}
