{"product_id": "39190", "page": 63, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-03", "text": "i grew up playing this game with my dad, and it's never lost it's charm. i love it. however, it took me a LONG time to figure out how to get it to actually work on my laptop, as it's not compatible with windows 7. i don't understand why they are selling it without being more clear about how to fix it so you can actually play it. i reccommend it though, because once you eventually get it to work, it's a great game. there's plenty on google to fix it so it's playable, and make sure to disable steam in-game and not to launch it from within steam.", "hours": 0.3, "username": "foxinthebox", "products": 82, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 63, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-02", "text": "Someone made a review about this game saying that it's not playable due to the graphics being a little outdated. Some classic games aren't played because of their graphics, they made sucess back in 2003 because they were innovative and the story and gameplay were satisfying. I'm not talking only about Dungeon Siege.. Prince of Persia the Trilogy is another exemple of a classic game with relatively bad graphics (compared to nowadays). That doesn't make a game bad though. I'm sure that if you haven't played a master piece like Dungeon Siege back in the release year, if you give a real try u'll see what I'm all about here.\nEverything in this game is good, specially the soundtrack, which is amazing!", "hours": 42.7, "username": "Liv", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
