{"product_id": "39190", "page": 64, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-23", "text": "Dungeon Siege\u00ae combines the immersive elements of a role-playing game with over-the-top intensity and non-stop action. Dungeon Siege plunges you into a continuous 3D fantasy world where you face off against an army of evil that has been unleashed.\nYou begin as a humble farmer, and as you travel through the world and gain new skills, you can gather a party of up to eight characters to aid you. Dungeon Siege impels the player into one over-the-top battle after the other as the storyline unfolds and a larger plot begins to reveal itself.\nA world of adventure where you can explore sprawling landscapes in a seamlessly unfolding story awaits...", "hours": 129.5, "username": "Tuong", "products": 2374, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 65, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-20", "text": "Closer to an adventure than an RPG, it's like Diablo but without the loot, the clicking, the atmosphere, or the character customization. It's an RPG-Lite dungeon crawler which is really a lot of fun. Of course, it's very dated at this stage, so only recommended for fans of the rpg-lite-diablo-esque-with-hardly-any-story-that-descends-into-tedium genre.", "hours": 7.6, "username": "Raennik", "products": 1278, "early_access": false}
