{"product_id": "39190", "page": 68, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-23", "text": "Although I haven't played Dungeon Siege much yet on my steam install I played through the entire game many time after the original release.  It is an excellent party based live action RPG (although you can pause while you make your character decisions if you want).  It is well worth the purchase for any fans of this style of RPG that may have missed it back in the day.", "hours": 0.1, "user_id": "76561198006657627", "username": "aderek79", "products": 307, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 68, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "Dungeon Siege represents a classic squad-based action role-playing game, which covers all bases with style. The accessible gameplay in combination with a broad spectrum of tactical customization allow you to create a team adapted to your own needs, offering plenty of variation and replayability.\nEven by today\u2019s standards it remains a decent example of original dungeon crawler game.\nThe game has no Steam achievements.", "hours": 23.6, "user_id": "76561197968514473", "username": "Meat-King\u00a9\u00ae", "products": 424, "early_access": false}
