{"product_id": "39190", "page": 68, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-12", "text": "WARNING: Steam did not impliment their own multiplayer for this game!\nYou can easily fix this with one quick google and a small download, though.\nStill, I do NOT recommend this as it's such an old game, albeit an awesome classic, and they did literally nothing to it, including no compatability or even slight graphics update. GPG & Steam in duo do not support it, making it mind boggling as to how this even made it on Steam to begin with.\nYou may as well go and get a copy of it for 50 cents at a hawk shop.\nWaste of money.", "hours": 19.5, "username": "\u039e\u044f\u044fo\u044f \u0298n\u0298", "products": 46, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39190", "page": 68, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-10", "text": "A fun classic dungeon crawler in the vein of Diablo, but with in depth party management and a better story.  The world is well built, finely detailed and fleshed out.  Explore off of the beaten path and you'll find all sorts of neat little nooks and crannies.  Combat is simple enough for managing a party of brave adventurers on a loot-filled quest, but satisfying.  This is a good, moderately old game.", "hours": 12.8, "username": "SubOptimizer", "products": 237, "early_access": false}
