{"product_id": "39190", "page": 75, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-01", "text": "Lost amongst the many hack and slash games that flooded the post Diablo market, Dungeon Siege deserves your love. Somewhere between Baldur's Gate and Diablo, you will control a party and can pause the action at any time, but loot lust and hacking/slashing abound. There are ways to get multiplayer working on Steam, but even if you are just in it for the single player, it's worth the price of admission.", "hours": 2.2, "username": "Antipunk", "products": 1290, "early_access": false}
